-- GAIL India to Spend $1.8 Billion Rupees to Double Chemical Unit's Capacity
-- B y   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 2010-09-22T06:16:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/gail-to-spend-1-8-billion-to-double-capacity-of-north-india-chemical-unit.html
GAIL India Ltd. , the countryâ€™s
monopoly natural gas distributor, plans to spend 81.4 billion
rupees ($1.8 billion) to double the capacity of its chemical
plant in the northern state of Uttar Pradesh.  The capacity of the Pata  chemical plant  will be increased
to 900,000 metric tons annually in three years, Chairman B.C.
Tripathi said, according to a copy of his speech to shareholders
in New Delhi today.  The company may spend 400 billion rupees by 2014-2015, when
its pipeline network will expand to 15,000 kilometers (9,325
miles) Tripathi said.  GAIL India has 7,847 kilometers of pipelines carrying
natural gas in the country, according to its  website .  Demand for gas may rise to 320 million cubic meters a day
by 2015, Tripathi said.  GAIL India plans to set up gas-based power plants and wind
and solar projects, Tripathi said. The company imported its
first spot cargo of liquefied natural gas in the current fiscal
year this week and plans to buy more cargoes in November and
December, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
